I'd like to begin by thanking everyone who did attend the commissioning, as well as those who submitted valid LOA's or inactivity notices. @everyone

Afternoon all, I wanted to inform you of some changes being made to written warnings and activity warnings.

**- Written Warnings,** will be issued for conduct related issues, such as disrespect, insubordination or improper uniform.
**- Activity Warnings,** will be issued for failing to react to a mandatory event (e.g inspections) as well as failing to attend an event that you have reacted with a checkmark too.

When you are issued with either warning, you will be given an appeal date, after which you can contact <@297072786046844938> or <@285897998150402049> to appeal the warning, you should express the fact that you understand why it was issued and we will determine whether it should be removed by looking at your behaviour / activity in the time period after the warning was issued.

Having a un-appealed written warning or two un-appealed activity warnings will make you ineligible to receive good conduct stripes and promotions, and hence I recommend you avoid receiving them.

This change comes in to try and increase the transparency of your current warnings, and upon receiving one you will be informed via a DM. However, in general - have some common sense, be a decent person and listen and you will be fine.

I would also like to reiterate our uniform and grooming standards: you should only be wearing uniform you have the right to wear (at your rank) that is sold by the Navy Quartermaster, and any facial hair should be a full beard or none at all. This means that any form of stubble or moustache is not allowed.

Any questions please do not hesitate to contact me.
